      "span_text": "FMD was significantly reduced in smokers (P, 0·05) and there was a significant positive relationship between n-3 PUFA status and FMD in smokers (P, 0·01), which was not present in non-smokers;. there were significant positive relationships between FMD and n-3 PUFA status in those subjects in the top one-third for fasting glucose, insulin and triacylglycerol levels with no relationships in those with lower levels;. neither plasma vitamin E concentrations (alone or adjusted for lipid concentrations) nor total antioxidant status were related to any of the measures of vascular function;. in the group as a whole, FMD was similar for the different endothelial NO synthase genotypes;. there were no significant differences in FMD between smokers and non-smokers with the Glu/Glu genotype, whereas in subjects with Glu/Asp and Asp/Asp genotypes the smokers had a significantly reduced FMD (P, 0·01;;. there was a significant relationship between n-3 PUFA status and FMD in Glu/Asp and Asp/Asp subjects (P, 0·05), but not in those with the Glu/Glu genotype"
